<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/245892-which-should-i-read-first-this-or-the">Which should I read first, this or The Hero and the Crown?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_245892'><a id="like_count_community_question_245892" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/245892?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">15 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F407813.The_Blue_Sword">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/245892-which-should-i-read-first-this-or-the">6 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/245892-which-should-i-read-first-this-or-the">See all 6 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/40627875-jason-holt"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1426907016i/40627875._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/40627875-jason-holt">Jason Holt</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">My wife and I read The Blue Sword first. The two books set up an inside joke. If you&apos;ve read The Hero and the Crown, then you can laugh at the people <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">My wife and I read The Blue Sword first. The two books set up an inside joke. If you've read The Hero and the Crown, then you can laugh at the people making a legend out of this ordinary person who was just fumbling around trying to do her best. And if you've read The Blue Sword, then you can laugh at this person fumbling around, not realizing that everything she does will become part of a heroic legend.<br /><br />So, yeah. It works either way.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
