<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/55772266-allipink"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1526410343i/55772266._UY100_CR16,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/55772266-allipink">Allipink</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I haven&apos;t ever read those books you mention, but I would not describe anything about this book as &quot;generic,&quot; and there are no love triangles. I don&apos;t <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I haven't ever read those books you mention, but I would not describe anything about this book as "generic," and there are no love triangles. I don't know what you're looking for in a book, but I would never hesitate to recommend The Blue Sword as an example of quality and depth of story and characterization.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
